{% if style_context %}
{% set has_memory = style_context.terminology_entries or style_context.temporary_glossary or style_context.do_not_use_terms %}
{% if has_memory %}
{% set flags = namespace(has_locked=false, has_soft=false) %}
{% for entry in style_context.temporary_glossary or [] %}
{% if entry.status == "locked" %}
{% set flags.has_locked = true %}
{% else %}
{% set flags.has_soft = true %}
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
DOCUMENT MEMORY USAGE:
- Use memory only when the same source term appears with the same meaning in the requested item.
- Prefer the longest matching source term first.
- Do not apply memory to unrelated longer/shorter phrases; never infer a shorter term translation from a longer term.
- Example: "Product Setup Guide" memory does not define "Product" alone.

{% if style_context.terminology_entries %}
LOCKED / PROVIDED TERMINOLOGY:
Use these translations exactly when the same source term appears with the same meaning:
{% for entry in style_context.terminology_entries %}
- {{ entry.source }}: {{ entry.target }}
{% endfor %}

{% endif %}
{% if flags.has_locked %}
LOCKED DOCUMENT TERMS:
Use these document-local translations exactly when the same source term appears with the same meaning:
{% for entry in style_context.temporary_glossary %}
{% if entry.status == "locked" %}
- {{ entry.source }}: {{ entry.target }}
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}

{% endif %}
{% if style_context.do_not_use_terms %}
CHUNK-SPECIFIC DO-NOT-USE TERMS:
Avoid these translations when the source term has the same document-local meaning:
{% for entry in style_context.do_not_use_terms %}
- {{ entry.source }}: {{ entry.targets }}
{% endfor %}

{% endif %}
{% if flags.has_soft %}
SOFT-LOCKED DOCUMENT TERMS:
Use these as preferred document-local translations; do not force them when context differs:
{% for entry in style_context.temporary_glossary %}
{% if entry.status != "locked" %}
- {{ entry.source }}: {{ entry.target }}
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}

{% endif %}
{% endif %}
{% endif %}
